						               													<description>A Picture is Worth a Thousand Words&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Imagym is a game which consists in drawing words your opponent will try to figure out and in figuring out the words your opponent will have drawn. In order to line up your tokens on the game board and to win the game, you will have to use your imagination as well as your sense of observation and of strategy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In turn, each opponent picks an indicator card and a 'difficulty' card, examines them, finds the word he/she has to draw on the game board and then places the cards, face down, in front of him/her. Each opponent draws his/her word on a sheet of his/her drawing pad. When all drawings are completed, each opponent shows his/her drawing to the others, long enough for them to try and figure out the word drawn. You get tokens for figuring out opponent word drawings and when they figure out your drawings.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Winner is the player or the team which is the first to line up 4 tokens on the game board, either horizontally, vertically or diagonally.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
